I've written three yang files, one is the module named mod.yang, one is the submodule, named suba.yang, and the last is another submodule named subb.yang.

```
module: mod
   +--rw name?      string
   +--rw a
   |  +--rw forsub?   string
   +--rw b?         -> /nameb
   +--rw namea?     string
   +--rw parent?    -> /name
   +--rw another?   -> /nameb
   +--rw nameb?     string
   +--rw upper?     -> /a/forsub
   +--rw other?     -> /namea
```

there are three leafs **'/name'**, **'/a/forsub/'**, **'/b'** in mod.yang, and **'/b'** is a reference of **'/nameb'** in submodule **'subb'**.

there are three leafs **'/namea'**, **'/parent'**, **'/another'** in suba.yang, and **'/parent'** is a reference of **'/name'** in module **'mod'**, **'/another'** is a reference of **'/nameb'** in submodule **'subb'**.

there are three leafs **'/nameb'**, **'/upper/'**, **'/other'** in subb.yang, and **'/upper'** is a reference of **'/a/forsub/'** in module **'mod'**, **'/other'** is a reference of **'/namea'** in submodule **'suba'**.

1. the mod could reference any leaf in it's sub modules, because the sub modules are included.
2. any submodule could reference the leafs in mod, but none of the sub modules include mod, and mod could not be included by sub mod right?
3. because the suba has a leaf **'/another'** reference to **'/nameb'** in **subb**, the suba.yang should include the subb.yang, or it report **suba.yang:15: error: mod:nameb in the path for another at mod.yang:23 (at suba.yang:13) is not found**.
4. because the subb has a leaf **'/other'** reference to **'/namea'** in **suba**, the subb.yang should include the suba.yang, or it report **subb.yang:16: error: mod:namea in the path for other at mod.yang:24 (at subb.yang:14) is not found**.
5. after suba and subb including each other, it report **subb.yang:3: error: circular dependency for module "suba"**

1. Why the submodules couldn't see each other, even both of them are included in mod?
2. How could I reference leafs between any two submodules without leading to the circular dependency?

PS:
mod.yang
```yang
module mod {
        namespace "http://www.none.com/conf/mod";
        prefix "mod";
        include suba;
        include subb;


        leaf name {
                type string;
        }   

        container a { 
                leaf forsub {
                        type string;
                }   
        }   

        leaf b { 
                type leafref {
                        path "/nameb";
                }   
        }   
        uses suba-grouping;
        uses subb-grouping;
}

```
suba.yang
```yang
submodule suba {
        belongs-to mod { prefix "mod";}
        include subb;

        grouping  suba-grouping {
                leaf namea {
                        type string;
                }   
                leaf parent {
                        type leafref {
                                path "/name";
                        }   
                }   
                leaf another {
                        type leafref {
                                path "/nameb";
                        }   
                }   
        }   
}

```
subb.yang
```yang
submodule subb {
        belongs-to mod { prefix "mod";}
        include suba;

        grouping  subb-grouping {
                leaf nameb {
                        type string;
                }   

                leaf upper {
                        type leafref {
                                path "/a/forsub";
                        }   
                }   
                leaf other {
                        type leafref {
                                path "/namea";
                        }   
                }   
        }   
}

```

Hi,

i'm having trouble converting bitmap object from java file to native files. I can convert bitmap object to array2d objects though.

and this is the code i get from someone's sitte to convert bitmap to array2d

void convertBitmapToArray2d(JNIEnv* env,
                            jobject bitmap,
                            array2d<rgb_pixel>& out) {
    AndroidBitmapInfo bitmapInfo;
    void* pixels;
    int state;

    if (0 > (state = AndroidBitmap_getInfo(env, bitmap, &bitmapInfo))) {
        LOGI("L%d: AndroidBitmap_getInfo() failed! error=%d", __LINE__, state);
        return;
    } else if (bitmapInfo.format != ANDROID_BITMAP_FORMAT_RGBA_8888) {
        LOGI("L%d: Bitmap format is not RGB_565!", __LINE__);
    }

    // Lock the bitmap for copying the pixels safely.
    if (0 > (state = AndroidBitmap_lockPixels(env, bitmap, &pixels))) {
        LOGI("L%d: AndroidBitmap_lockPixels() failed! error=%d", __LINE__, state);
        return;
    }

    LOGI("L%d: info.width=%d, info.height=%d", __LINE__, bitmapInfo.width, bitmapInfo.height);
    out.set_size((long) bitmapInfo.height, (long) bitmapInfo.width);

    char* line = (char*) pixels;
    for (int h = 0; h < bitmapInfo.height; ++h) {
        for (int w = 0; w < bitmapInfo.width; ++w) {
            uint32_t* color = (uint32_t*) (line + 4 * w);

            out[h][w].red = (unsigned char) (0xFF & ((*color) >> 24));
            out[h][w].green = (unsigned char) (0xFF & ((*color) >> 16));
            out[h][w].blue = (unsigned char) (0xFF & ((*color) >> 8));
        }

        line = line + bitmapInfo.stride;
    }

    // Unlock the bitmap.
    AndroidBitmap_unlockPixels(env, bitmap);
}

