Hello there. I experienced a segfault when loading a .ASE file. Apparently, two nodes were referring each other. I avoided the segfault with this simple patch:

```
diff --git a/code/ASELoader.cpp b/code/ASELoader.cpp
index 3a78e06..13bfb5f 100644
--- a/code/ASELoader.cpp
+++ b/code/ASELoader.cpp
@@ -579,7 +579,7 @@ void ASEImporter::AddNodes (const std::vector<BaseNode*>& nodes,
                node->mTransformation = mParentAdjust*snode->mTransform;

                // Add sub nodes - prevent stack overflow due to recursive parenting
-           if (node->mName != node->mParent->mName) {
+         if (node->mName != node->mParent->mName && node->mName != node->mParent->mParent->mName) {
                        AddNodes(nodes,node,node->mName.data,snode->mTransform);
                }
```

 but I have no idea whatsoever if this is the proper way to solve the problem. I can submit a pull request if needed. Let me know...

